```json
{"tool":"write_file","args":{"path":"docs/PINOUT.md","content":"# PINOUT: USB-C Power Breakout\n\nStage 4 (schematic). Net/pin assignments as built in\n`usb-c-power-breakout.kicad_sch`. Net names match SUBSYSTEMS §1 exactly:\n`VBUS`, `VBUS_PROT`, `GND`, `CC1`, `CC2`, plus the internal LED node\n`LED_A` (R3→D2 anode).\n\n## Strapping / boot pins\n\n**None.** This board has no MCU, no programmable logic, and no boot/strap\npins (SUBSYSTEMS §8: MCU absent). There is therefore no strapping table to\nsatisfy — CC termination is two passive resistors, not a configurable pin.\nRecorded so the absence is not read as a missing check.\n\n## Net map\n\n| Net | Pins on net | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| VBUS | J1.A4 (VBUS), D1.1 (TVS anode), F1.1 | Raw 5V from receptacle, pre-protection. TVS clamps here. |\n| VBUS_PROT | F1.2, R3.1, J2.1, J3.1, J3.2 | Post-PTC protected 5V rail → LED branch + both outputs. |\n| GND | J1.A1 (GND), D1.2, R1.2, R2.2, D2.1 (K), J2.2, J3.3, J3.4 | Common ground / TVS + LED return. |\n| CC1 | J1.A5, R1.1 | Rd 5.1k pulldown, orientation A. |\n| CC2 | J1.B5, R2.1 | Rd 5.1k pulldown, orientation B (independent from CC1). |\n| LED_A | R3.2, D2.2 (A) | Internal node: LED series resistor → LED anode. |\n\n## J1 USB-C unused pins (no-connect, intentional)\n\n| Pin | Signal | Handling |\n|---|---|---|\n| A6 | D+ | no_connect — no USB data (SPEC §6). |\n| A7 | D- | no_connect — no USB data (SPEC §6). |\n| A8 | SBU1 | no_connect — unused sideband. |\n| B8 | SBU2 | no_connect — unused sideband. |\n| S1 | SHIELD | no_connect at schematic; chassis/shield handling deferred to layout (may be stitched to GND on PCB). |\n\n## Connector pinouts (user-facing)\n\n| Connector | Pin | Signal |\n|---|---|---|\n| J2 screw (3.5mm) | 1 | VBUS_PROT (+5V) |\n| J2 screw (3.5mm) | 2 | GND |\n| J3 header 2x2 | 1,2 (top row) | VBUS_PROT (+5V) |\n| J3 header 2x2 | 3,4 (bottom row) | GND |\n\n## Notes\n\n- The USB-C symbol models a single VBUS and single GND pin for schematic\n  clarity; the physical receptacle parallels 4x VBUS / 4x GND contacts to\n  share 3A (SUBSYSTEMS §2). Footprint pad→net paralleling is applied at the\n  layout stage. This is a schematic-level simplification, not a change to\n  the 3A copper/connector rating (SPEC §3.1).\n- MH1/MH2 mounting holes carry no electrical net (SUBSYSTEMS §7).\n- \"3A\" is a copper/connector/protection *rating*, not negotiated current;\n  no PD/CC logic is implied by CC1/CC2 (SPEC §3.1).\n"}}
